CC BY 4.0 — Adventurer avatar assets
=====================================

Source: Adventurer by Lisa Wischofsky
        https://www.figma.com/community/file/1184595184137881796
Designer: Lisa Wischofsky — https://www.instagram.com/lischi_art/
Distributed via: DiceBear (https://www.dicebear.com/styles/adventurer),
        @dicebear/adventurer npm package v9.4.3
License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
        https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

These SVG layers are extracted from the `@dicebear/adventurer` package's
component source (`lib/components/*.js`), which itself packages Lisa
Wischofsky's original Figma artwork for programmatic use. The files in this
directory are a derivative work: split back out into standalone per-layer
SVGs and, where the source parameterized a fill color (base skin tone, hair
color), recolored to `fill="currentColor"` so each layer can be recolored by
whatever consumes it.

CC BY 4.0 permits this — sharing and adapting for any purpose, including
commercially — provided that:

  1. Attribution is given to Lisa Wischofsky as the original artist, with a
     link to this license. See the credit line in this repo's main README
     and in the `leaf-writer` repo's THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md.
  2. Changes are indicated. This notice does that: assets here are modified
     (split into layers, recolored to currentColor) from the original
     Adventurer artwork.
  3. No additional restrictions are placed on downstream use beyond what
     CC BY 4.0 itself permits.

The `@dicebear/adventurer` package's own code (the JS that composes these
layers, not the artwork) is separately MIT licensed, copyright Florian
Körner. That MIT code is not vendored here — this directory contains only
the extracted artwork.
